            <title>[SPARK-7615] MLLIB Word2Vec wordVectors divided by Euclidean Norm equals to zero </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7615</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Word2VecModel, wordVecNorms may contains Euclidean Norm equals to zero. This will cause incorrect calculation for cosine distance. when you do cosineVec(ind) / wordVecNorms(ind). Cosine distance should be equal to 0 for norm = 0. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
